A blank character at the end of the {{java.date.picker.java.format}} line (i.e. after the value in the name=value pair) in jira-application.properties results in JIRA rejecting a date with the valid date format in a date picker. See the attached image.

Looking at the code, it seems that we do not trim() when we read in properties from jira-application.properties. So my guess this bug is somewhat broader than just {{java.date.picker.java.format}}, however I haven't tested with a blank character at the end of any other entries. I'd like to, but it is late on Friday and I'm away on Monday, and I've got enough already for this to be a bug. I'm happy to help later next week if you would like me to investigate more for other entries.

